[hr][hr]

[center][b][size=5]🔍 LootPulse[/size][/b][/center]
[center]Press [b]F[/b] to pulse-scan all valuables in range — discover brackets and map icons, instantly.[/center]

[hr]

[b][size=4]✨ What it does[/size][/b]

LootPulse is a valuable scanner for R.E.P.O. Press the configured key to locate all valuable objects within the defined radius, trigger the game's native discovery effect (yellow brackets) on each one, and automatically register them on the map.

No item stays hidden.

[hr]

[b][size=4]📡 Features[/size][/b]

[list]
[*][b]Key-triggered scan[/b] — press F (configurable) to pulse immediately
[*][b]Visual brackets[/b] — triggers the game's native discovery animation on each valuable found
[*][b]Map icons[/b] — all scanned valuables appear on the map automatically
[*][b]Configurable radius[/b] — set the scan range from 5 to 200 meters
[*][b]Configurable cooldown[/b] — prevents scan spam (0 to 60 seconds)
[*][b]Resilient to game updates[/b] — critical APIs resolved via reflection; automatic fallbacks if the game updates
[*][b]Detailed logs[/b] — know exactly how many items were found and processed
[/list]

[hr]

[b][size=4]👥 Multiplayer[/size][/b]

[b]Each player needs to install the mod[/b] to see the effects on their own screen. The scan is processed locally — each client acts independently.

[list]
[*][b]Only host has the mod[/b] — only the host sees brackets and map updates; other players see nothing
[*][b]Everyone has the mod[/b] — each player uses their own scanner independently
[*][b]Nobody has the mod[/b] — no changes to the game
[/list]

[hr]

[b][size=4]⚙️ Configuration[/size][/b]

Edit [font=Courier New]BepInEx/config/com.hiarlyscripter.repo.lootpulse.cfg[/font] or use [b]REPOConfig[/b] in-game:

[b]ScanKey[/b] [i](Section: Scanner · default: F)[/i]
Key that triggers the scanner. Supports any keyboard key.

[b]ScanRange[/b] [i](Section: Scanner · default: 30 · range: 5–200)[/i]
Detection radius in meters. Use larger values to sweep the entire level.

[b]CooldownSeconds[/b] [i](Section: Scanner · default: 4 · range: 0–60)[/i]
Minimum seconds between consecutive scans. Zero disables the cooldown.

[b]EnableVisualBrackets[/b] [i](Section: Scanner · default: true)[/i]
Displays discovery brackets on the valuables found.

[b]EnableMapIcons[/b] [i](Section: Scanner · default: true)[/i]
Adds valuable icons to the map when scanning.

[b]RequireLevelOrRun[/b] [i](Section: Scanner · default: true)[/i]
Only allows scanning during active runs (generated level). Disable only for testing outside a level.

[b]VerboseLogging[/b] [i](Section: Scanner · default: false)[/i]
Logs details of each individually processed item to BepInEx.LogOutput.log.

[hr]

[b][size=4]📦 Requirements[/size][/b]

[b]Required[/b]
[list]
[*][b]BepInExPack 5.4.23.5[/b] — base framework for R.E.P.O. mods
[/list]

[b]Optional[/b]
[list]
[*][b]REPOConfig[/b] — edit settings inside the game without opening config files
[/list]

No other dependencies. LootPulse only uses the game's native APIs.

[hr]

[b][size=4]🛠️ Installation[/size][/b]

[b]Manual installation (Vortex):[/b]
[list]
[*]Install [b]BepInExPack[/b] first
[*]Use the [b]Mod Manager Download[/b] button on Nexus — Vortex installs automatically into the correct structure
[*]Or manually: extract and copy the [font=Courier New]BepInEx/[/font] folder to the game directory
[/list]

The config file will be generated automatically at [font=Courier New]BepInEx/config/com.hiarlyscripter.repo.lootpulse.cfg[/font] on first run.

[hr]

[b][size=4]❓ Troubleshooting[/size][/b]

[b]Pressing F does nothing[/b]
Confirm the mod loaded by opening [font=Courier New]BepInEx/LogOutput.log[/font] and searching for [font=Courier New][LootPulse][/font]. Also make sure you're inside an active level (not the menu or lobby).

[b]Brackets appear but map doesn't update[/b]
The map API may have changed after a game update. Report as a bug with the full log — the mod has automatic fallbacks for most changes.

[b]Key conflict with another mod[/b]
Change [b]ScanKey[/b] in the config file to a key without conflicts.

[b]Mod doesn't load[/b]
Verify [b]BepInExPack[/b] is installed and active. Check [font=Courier New]BepInEx/LogOutput.log[/font] for error messages.

